    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-08-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <head>487. National Security Action Memorandum No. 259<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d487fn1">Source: Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Meetings
                        and Memoranda, NSAM 259. Secret. Information copies were sent to the
                        Secretaries of Defense and the Treasury and the Director, Bureau of the
                        Budget.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-08-20">August 20, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Director, Agency for International Development</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_AID1">Aid</gloss> Program for Laos—FY 64</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has approved the proposed FY 64 <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                    Program for Laos presented in Aidto X–200,<note n="1" xml:id="d487fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d485fn2">footnote 2, Document 485</ref>.</note> subject to the
                    following additional action: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Sale of dollars for kip on the open market is to be supervised by an
                            American expert in Vientiane.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>An agreement with the Lao Government is to be made to hold the budget,
                            and particularly defense expenditures, at current levels.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>An experienced non-American, non-Lao should be placed in the Laos
                            finance ministry, who is to see that the Lao budget is kept under
                            control and deficit financing is prevented which would neutralize the
                            proposed open-market dollar transactions.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>The President desires to be informed of actions taken to implement the
                            above.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
